Grape Seed Oil - Different Health advantages



Using grapes and its oil could be traced to the first Egyptian civilisation. The sap from the grapevine was used for various medicinal benefits including treating small pox and cancer. The grape seed oil has been around use since several decades. The oil is actually the by- product that remains following the wine-making process.

The grape seed oil is mainly produced in Italy though it can also be manufactured in other areas of the country such as Argentina, Spain and France. It's identified as light colored oil that is thin in consistency. It has a nutty flavour and a sweet smell. The early European folk healers used the seed oil for stopping diseases for example cholera, cancer, sore eyes, constipation, liver and kidney diseases.

